<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="iddc5b0813-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0"><ref href="/us/pl/96/221/s309/b/1">Section 309(b)(1) of Pub. L. 96–221</ref> redesignated subch. III as title III of <ref href="/us/act/1934-06-26/ch750">act June 26, 1934, ch. 750</ref>, cited as a credit to this section.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="iddc5b0814-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2006—<ref href="/us/pl/109/351">Pub. L. 109–351</ref> substituted “section 1752a(d)” for “section 1752a(e)”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="iddc5b0815-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="iddc5b0816-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1979-10-01">Oct. 1, 1979</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/95/630/s1806">section 1806 of Pub. L. 95–630</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t12/s1795">section 1795 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
